profile_positions.description:
Atos SE (Societas Europaea) is a leader in digital services. Serving a global client base, the Group provides Consulting & Systems Integration services, Managed Services & BPO, Cloud operations, Big Data & Cyber-security solutions, as well as transactional services through Worldline.

As director of business development digital signage & big data and analytics for regions Benelux and Scandinavia responsible for the end-2-end development of propositions for customers and prospects in two areas: big data and analytics and digital signage. 

My activities, responsibility and achievements includes:
-	Being a trusted advisor;
-	Perform inspiration workshops;
-	Create use cases and value added solutions; 
-	Initiate and act on proactive sales and marketing;
-	Liaison and collaborate with ISV partners;
-	Create and develop propositions; 
-	Create and monitor the sales funnel across service lines;
-	Business planning;
-	Leading a sales team;
-	Support local and international account management;
-	Targeted order intake and external revenue;
-	Represent Atos at conventions and seminars. 

Digital Signage:
-	Created solutions that improves the customer journey, experience (UE) and satisfaction (CSAT), efficiency of processes, increase of sales at lower cost and creates huge amount of valuable information (Big Data, Customer Intelligence); 
-	Active with this Omni-channel marketing approach in the markets in Financial Services, Retail, FMCG, CPG and Telecom;
-	Created innovative solutions: financial branch of the future, store of the future and bar of the future;
-	Recently a major bank in Belgium implemented the Digital Information Wall in one of their flagship stores and their rest of the branches will follow soon; 
-	For a large beverage manufacturer the first prototypes for their bar of the future are delivered; 
-	Created innovative solutions for Danish DIY retail, but also for paint manufacturers for instore DIY POS solutions in the Netherlands.

Facilicom Services Group, is a facilities provider active in the field of cleaning, security, airport services, catering, employment agencies, facilities management, construction & contracting, and catering services throughout Western Europe. Facilicom Services Group employs about 30,000 people in the Netherlands, Belgium, France and United Kingdom, and has an annual turnover of € 1 billion (2012)

My activities, responsibility and achievements includes:
-	Managed the international IT group, direct reports: Business Information Management (BIM), Project Management Office (PMO), IT Services Department ( ITSM, 24x7, application management, system development, infrastructure management), SAP Competence Manager and  the IT country managers;
-	Successfully reorganized the IT department in demand-operate-manage with a clear focus on customer satisfaction and operational and cost efficiency;
-	Stayed and kept within agreed IT budget, externally benchmarked;
-	Realized new IT governance structure and procedures;
-	Aligned the IT strategy to the business strategy;
-	Succeeded to support new business services by IT innovation;
-	Advised the Management Board;
-	Setup a new group portal;
-	Setup a new business intelligence system;
-	Initiated an ERP program (SAP) to replace legacy systems (AS400);
-	Managed a SAP Competence Centre;
-	Realized targetted and benchmarked customer satisfaction;
-	Managed relationships towards both external and internal clients and IT vendors.

2000-2006 Competence Director Enterprise Content Management (ECM) Consultancy
   - C-level advice, architecture design and acquisition of ECM projects in financial, 
       chemical industry, postal, energy. Main focus on publishing market;
   - Realized new services and  accomplished targeted growth;
   - Alliance management of ECM vendors;
   - Sales, account and competence management;
   - ECM Business planning and strategy.

1997-2000 Competence Director Business Intelligence (BI) Consultancy
   - advice, architecture design and acquisition of Data Warehouse and BI projects in waste management industry, airline industry, retail, postal and publishing market;
   - Accomplished targeted growth;
   - Alliance management of BI vendors;
   - Sales, account and competence management;
   - BI services business planning and strategy.

1995-1997 Manager Windows Research Centre, Client/Server expert
   - Managing the department
   - Development and maintenance of class libraries to improve application development time and cycles.
